title: Employee Handbook 2024
content:
Welcome to our Employee Handbook. This comprehensive guide covers all company policies, 
            procedures, and benefits. Topics include vacation policy, sick leave, remote work guidelines, 
            professional development opportunities, health insurance, retirement plans, and code of conduct. 
            All employees are required to read and understand these policies. The handbook is updated annually 
            to reflect changes in company policy and legal requirements. Please contact HR for any questions.

title: IT Security Policy
content:
Information Technology Security Policy: All employees must follow these security guidelines. 
            Password requirements: minimum 12 characters, must include uppercase, lowercase, numbers and symbols. 
            Multi-factor authentication is mandatory for all systems. Never share passwords or leave computers unlocked. 
            Report suspicious emails immediately. VPN usage is required when working remotely. Regular security 
            training is mandatory. Data encryption is required for sensitive information. Violation of security 
            policies may result in disciplinary action.

title: Remote Work Guidelines
content:
Remote work policy effective 2024: Employees may work remotely up to 3 days per week. 
            Core hours are 10 AM to 3 PM in your local timezone. Daily standup meetings are required. 
            Home office equipment allowance is $500 per year. Internet reimbursement up to $50 monthly. 
            Productivity tracking tools must be installed. Regular check-ins with managers are mandatory. 
            Maintain professional background for video calls. Ensure secure home network setup. 
            Emergency contact information must be updated.

title: Benefits Overview
content:
Company Benefits Package includes: Health insurance with zero deductible, dental and vision coverage. 
            401k matching up to 6 percent. Unlimited PTO policy after first year. Professional development budget 
            of $2000 annually. Gym membership reimbursement. Mental health support through Employee Assistance Program. 
            Parental leave 12 weeks paid. Life insurance 2x annual salary. Stock options for all employees. 
            Commuter benefits. Free lunch on Fridays. Annual company retreat.

title: Code of Conduct
content:
Professional Code of Conduct: Treat all colleagues with respect and dignity. 
            Harassment of any kind will not be tolerated. Maintain confidentiality of company information. 
            Avoid conflicts of interest. Report violations immediately to HR or use anonymous hotline. 
            Dress code is business casual. Social media policy: do not share confidential information. 
            Gift policy: report gifts over $50. Fair and ethical business practices are mandatory. 
            Discrimination based on any protected class is strictly prohibited.

title: Project List.docx
content:
ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
Project Title: Building Intelligent Application with Azure AI Search 
Description: Design and implement Azure Intelligent Search Application which will be used in the internal self-service portal for the employees to search content and documents based on natural language processing. Use Azure native service like Azure AI Search to utilise the AI powered solution provided by Azure. Use an optimised and efficient ML model to train AI Search.
 CYBER SECURITY
Project title: Developing a Threat Intelligence Platform for a Smart City   
Description: Identify and analyse cyber threats in real-time. Predict and prevent potential attacks on critical infrastructure. Enhance incident response and reduce mean time to detect (MTTD) and respond (MTTR). Improve situational awareness for smart city stakeholders.
Project Title: Securing a Smart Home Ecosystem
Description: a) Enhancing a Smart Home Security Posture Focus: Analyse and significantly improve the security posture of a typical smart home ecosystem against common and emerging cyber threats. b) Develop Proactive threat detection and protective mechanism Focus: Design and implement proactive mechanisms for detecting malicious activities and enabling swift responses within the smart home network. c) Educating Users on Smart Home Security Best Practices Focus: Create user-friendly educational materials and strategies to promote security awareness and responsible usage of smart home devices. Activities: Develop guidelines and best practices for secure configuration and usage of smart home devices. Design training modules to educate users about common threats and mitigation techniques. Explore methods for delivering timely security updates and advisories to smart home users.
Project title: Securing a Vulnerable Web Application
Description: Gain practical experience in identifying, understanding, and safely exploiting common web application vulnerabilities as defined by the OWASP top 10. Apply fundamental security controls and best practices to mitigate identified web application vulnerabilities. Create foundational documentation for secure web application development and a basic incident response plan for web application attacks.
Project title: Setting Up a Secure Network for a Small Branch Office
Description: Design and implement a secure, segmented Local Area Network (LAN) for a simulated small branch office environment, protecting internal resources and user data. Set up secure remote access capabilities for branch office employees and implement robust user authentication mechanisms across the network. Deploy essential endpoint security measures on client machines and establish basic network monitoring for security events.
DATA ANALYTICS
PROJECT TITLE: Data Mart Loading & Credit Rating Reporting
Description: Design and implement a Data Mart Loading and Credit Rating Reporting that provides actionable insights into credit rating trends of different securities, countries, companies and help in meaningful predictions and projections on future credit rating changes. The system leverages data processing, transforming and analytics to populate data mart tables into standard type 2 format of SCD. This system enables different services like adhoc or batch queries on credit rating, credit rating historical trends and future predictions and more.
Project title: Market Data Analytics Price Challenge Reporting
Description: Design and implement a Market Data Analytics Price Challenge Reporting that provides actionable insights into price trends and efficiency of market data providers, vendor performance and helps provide feedback for possible error correction in pricing mechanism. The system leverages data processing, transforming and analytics to do a comparison of different market data feeds. This system enables the data consumer and client to measure efficiency of the data provider.
Project title: Developing a Threat Intelligence Platform for a Smart City
Description: Build a security master data based on other pricing feeds which already has security related information in some shape or form. The idea is to select, correct and clean the information based on majority voting algorithm. If there are conflicts in any value, the value proposed by majority of the vendor is considered as true and becomes a part of the master data.
DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM
Project title: Adhoc Security Pricing
Description: Create a robust system which will provide security pricing for adhoc securities for a given date or date range, along with other security details. It will accept both file upload or text as input data and price comparison.
Project title: Campaign Management System
Description: Design and implement a Campaign Management System that provides progress, outcome of different campaigns, provide insights on success of campaign and planning future campaigns. The system leverages data processing, transforming and analytics to populate data mart tables that will help in reporting, deriving insights and take decisions on campaigns. This system enables different services like adhoc queries, adhoc reporting, and taking business decisions on campaigns.
Project title: Community Volunteer Connect 
Description: Design, develop, and implement a functional, database-driven web application to connect local volunteers with non-profit organisations. This project will provide hands-on experience in the complete lifecycle of a database system, from conceptual data modelling and normalisation to implementing a secure, multi-user application that performs complex queries and transactions.
Project title: Corporate Action Reporting
Description: Create an application that reports corporate actions for different countries, exchange and date range. This helps in determining the security master derivation, validation, credit rating and other financial service auditing.
Project title: Customer Profitability Analysis
Description: Design and implement a Customer Profitability Analysis that provides the profitability metrics of a customer. The system leverages data processing, transforming and analytics to populate data mart tables that will help in reporting, deriving insights and take decisions on customer profitability analysis. This system enables different services like adhoc queries, adhoc reporting, and it helps in retaining the profitable customer or customer segment by identifying them.
Project title: Data Mart Loading and Security Audit Pricing
Description: Design and implement a Data Mart Loading and Security Audit Pricing that provides actionable insights into audit pricing trends of different securities, fixed income pricing and help in meaningful predictions and projections on future pricing changes. The system leverages data processing, transforming and analytics to populate data mart tables into standard type 2 format of SCD. This system enables different services like adhoc or batch queries on audit pricing and market pricing variations and more.
Project title: Fund Index Analysis
Description: Create a robust system which will compare the fund performance against any chosen market index and its trends. This will help to benchmark the fund performance and take further actions.
Project title: Online Course Enrolment and Progress Tracking System
Description: Design and implement a relational database system that manages course enrolments, tracks student progress, and generates performance reports for an online learning platform using SQL and DBMS principles.
Project title: Superstore Profit Analytics
Description: Analyse historical sales data from a fictional retail superstore to identify key drivers of sales and profitability. The ultimate goal is to provide actionable, data-backed recommendations to the store's management to help optimise marketing strategies, improve inventory management, and increase overall profitability.
Project title: University Hostel Management System
Description: Design, develop, and implement a relational database system for managing the operations of a university hostel. This project will provide hands-on experience in the complete database development life cycle, from conceptual design to implementation, querying, and reinforcing core DBMS concepts learned in the classroom.
OOPs CONCEPT
Project title: Personal Finance Tracker
Description: Design and implement a Personal Finance Tracker using Object-oriented Programming (OOP) principles in C++/Java/Python. The system will enable users to manage their income, expenses, budget, and generate monthly financial summaries. The solution has to be built using well-structured classes and objects, demonstrating key OOP concepts such as encapsulation, inheritance, polymorphism, and abstraction to model real-world financial operations effectively.
WEB TECHNOLOGY
Project title: Online Event Booking and Management
Description: Design and develop a responsive Online Event Booking and Management System using modern web technologies. The system will allow users to browse, book, and manage events, while providing organisers with tools to create and monitor their events.
Project title: Smart Feedback Collection and Analysis System
Description: Build a full-stack web application that enables users to submit feedback through a responsive frontend interface, processes the input in the backend using sentiment analysis, stores the data in a structured database, and visualises the results using dynamic web-based charts. The system will demonstrate an integration of core web technologies including HTML, CSS, JavaScript, RESTful APIs, backend frameworks, and database management.

title: GATE 2026 CS SYLLABUS.pdf
content:
GATE 2026                                                                                         IIT Guwahati | Organizing  Institute         
 
 
CS Computer Science and Information Technology                             
Section  1: Engineering  Mathematics  
Discrete Mathematics:  Propositional and first order logic. Sets, relations, functions, partial orders and 
lattices. Monoids, Groups. Graphs: connectivity, matching, colouring. Combinatorics: counting, 
recurrence relations, generating functions.  
Linear Algebra: Matrices, determi nants, system of linear equations, eigenvalues and eigenvectors, LU 
decomposition.  
Calculus:  Limits, continuity and differentiability, Maxima and minima, Mean value theorem, 
Integration.  
Probability  and Statistics:  Random variables, Uniform, normal, exponential, Poisson and binomial  
distributions. Mean, median, mode and standard deviation. Conditional probability and Bayes theorem.  
Section  2: Digital  Logic  
Boolean algebra. Combinational and sequential circuits. Minimization. Number representations and  
computer arithmetic (fixed and floating point).  
Section  3: Computer  Organization  and Architecture  
Machine instructions and addressing modes. ALU, data‐path and control unit. Instruction pipelining, 
pipeline hazards. Memory hierarchy: cache, main memory an d secondary storage; I/O interface 
(interrupt and DMA mode).  
Section  4: Programming  and Data  Structures  
Programming in C. Recursion. Arrays, stacks, queues, linked lists, trees, binary search trees, binary 
heaps, graphs.  
Section  5: Algorithms  
Searching, sorting, hashing. Asymptotic worst case time and space complexity. Algorithm design 
techniques: greedy, dynamic programming and divide‐and‐conquer. Graph traversals, minimum 
spanning trees, shortest paths.  
Section  6: Theory  of Computation  
Regular expressions and finite automata. Context -free grammars and push -down automata. Regular  and 
context -free languages, pumping lemma. Turing machines and undecidability.  
Section  7: Compiler  Design  
Lexical analysis, parsing, syntax -directed translation. Runtime  environments. Intermediate code 
generation. Local optimi zation, Data flow analyses: constant propagation, liveness analysis, common 
sub expression elimination.  
Section  8: Operating  System  
System calls, processes, threads, inter‐process communication, conc urrency and synchronization. 
Deadlock. CPU and I/O scheduling. Memory management and virtual memory. File systems.  
Section  9: Databases  
ER‐model. Relational model: relational algebra, tuple calculus, SQL. Integrity constraints, normal 
forms. File organization, indexing (e.g., B and B+ trees). Transactions and concurrency control.  
 
GATE 2026                                                                                         IIT Guwahati | Organizing  Institute         
 
 
Section  10: Computer  Networks  
Concept of layering: OSI and TCP/IP Protocol Stacks; Basics of packet, circuit and virtual circuit - 
switching; Data link layer: framing, error detection, Medium Access Control, Ethernet bridging; 
Routing protocols: shortest path, flooding, distance vector and link state routing; Fragmentation and IP 
addressing, IPv4, CIDR notation, Basics of IP support protocols (ARP, DHCP, ICMP), Network 
Address Translation (NAT); Transport layer: flow c ontrol and congestion control, UDP, TCP, sockets; 
Application layer protocols: DNS, SMTP, HTTP, FTP, Email .
